    "description_long": "This is a Siemens SIPROTEC control cabinet, typically used in power distribution and automation systems. The front panel features a large green display area, numerous labeled buttons, indicator lights, and rotary switches, all set within a light gray and blue frame. The rear side is densely populated with multiple terminal blocks for electrical connections, each labeled for organized wiring. The cabinet is constructed from sturdy sheet metal, likely steel, with a matte finish and minimal surface texture. Small warning and information labels are visible on the front, indicating operational and safety information. The overall design is boxy and robust, suitable for installation in technical rooms or substations.",
